# DocuMind — Enterprise Document Intelligence RAG System

## What This Is

A production-grade full-stack RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) app that lets users upload any PDF documents (research papers, SOPs, tech docs, HR handbooks), builds a vector index, and answers questions with inline citations.

**Repo**: github.com/GogulaAkhila/documind

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend | Django 5.1 + DRF + Django Channels (Daphne ASGI) |
| Frontend | React 19 + TypeScript + Vite 8 + Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui |
| State | Zustand + TanStack Query |
| LLM | Google Gemini 2.5 Flash (via REST API — NOT langchain_google_genai) |
| Embeddings | Google Gemini Embedding 001 (768 dims) with sentence-transformers fallback |
| Vector DB | Supabase PostgreSQL + pgvector (IVFFlat index, lists=1 for small datasets) |
| Re-ranker | Jina Reranker v2 |
| PDF Parsing | PyMuPDF (fitz) — NOT unstructured (causes SIGSEGV on macOS) |
| Task Queue | Celery + Redis (Upstash, TLS via rediss://) |
| Evaluation | RAGAS |

## Architecture

```
Frontend (Vite :5173) → REST API → Django (Daphne :8000)
                                      ├── RAG Pipeline
                                      │   ├── Query Expansion (Gemini)
                                      │   ├── Hybrid Retrieval (pgvector dense + PostgreSQL FTS + RRF)
                                      │   ├── Jina Reranker (top 20 → top 5)
                                      │   ├── Generation (Gemini 2.5 Flash)
                                      │   └── Hallucination Guardrail (Gemini)
                                      ├── Celery Worker → Document Ingestion
                                      └── Supabase (pgvector + Django ORM tables)
```

## Implemented Features

- Semantic chunking with section detection (academic + enterprise patterns)
- Hybrid retrieval: dense vector search + PostgreSQL full-text search with reciprocal rank fusion
- Jina Reranker v2 (top 20 → top 5)
- Multi-query expansion via Gemini
- Answer generation with inline citations [Document Title, Page X]
- Hallucination guardrail (post-generation grounding check)
- Document upload with async processing via Celery
- Collections for grouping documents
- Chat sessions with message history
- RAGAS evaluation framework
- Embedding fallback: Gemini → local sentence-transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, 384 dims)
- Enterprise document support: SOPs, tech docs, handbooks (not just research papers)
- UI revamp: semantic color tokens (info/success/warning/danger) with dark mode support
- UI revamp: collections dashboard with colored icon tiles, search, aggregate stats, three-dot menu
- UI revamp: collection detail with side-by-side documents/chats panels, quick ask input
- UI revamp: chat with inline citation chips, collapsible sources sidebar, feedback actions, model badge
- UI revamp: document upload with 4-stage pipeline stepper, batch summary, retry on failure
- UI revamp: delete confirmations for collections and documents
- UI revamp: chat history sidebar with active session highlighting

## Critical Implementation Details

### Gemini API calls use REST, NOT langchain_google_genai
The `langchain_google_genai` package uses the deprecated `google.generativeai` gRPC library which has blocking/key issues. All LLM calls (generation, query expansion, guardrails, embeddings) use direct `httpx` REST calls to `generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta`.

### macOS Celery must use --pool=solo
PyMuPDF's C libraries crash with Celery's default prefork pool. Always start Celery with:
```bash
OBJC_DISABLE_INITIALIZE_FORK_SAFETY=YES celery -A config.celery worker -l info --pool=solo
```

### Shell GEMINI_API_KEY overrides .env
If GEMINI_API_KEY is set in the shell environment, it overrides python-dotenv. Always `unset GEMINI_API_KEY` before starting Daphne/Celery, or remove it from ~/.zshrc.

### IVFFlat index lists must be small for small datasets
The pgvector IVFFlat index uses `lists=1`. With few documents (<1000 vectors), higher list counts cause empty search results. Scale lists as: `max(1, n_vectors / 1000)`.

### Embedding dimension must be consistent
Gemini embeddings = 768 dims, local model = 384 dims. Mixing models between ingestion and query causes "different vector dimensions" errors. If switching models, re-process all documents.

### Upstash Redis TLS
Upstash uses `rediss://` (TLS). Celery needs SSL config in settings:
```python
if CELERY_BROKER_URL.startswith("rediss://"):
    import ssl as _celery_ssl
    CELERY_BROKER_USE_SSL = {"ssl_cert_reqs": _celery_ssl.CERT_REQUIRED}
    CELERY_REDIS_BACKEND_USE_SSL = {"ssl_cert_reqs": _celery_ssl.CERT_REQUIRED}
```

## Project Structure

```
backend/
  config/settings/{base,development,production}.py
  apps/{documents,chat,evaluation}/  — Django apps with models, views, serializers, URLs
  core/rag/{chunking,embeddings,retrieval,reranker,query_expansion,generation,guardrails,pipeline}.py
  core/vectorstore/pgvector_store.py  — Direct SQL against Supabase pgvector
  core/utils/citations.py

frontend/src/
  hooks/{use-collections,use-documents,use-chat,use-evaluation}.ts  — TanStack Query
  stores/{chat-store,document-store,ui-store}.ts  — Zustand
  components/{chat,collections,documents,evaluation,layout}/
  lib/{api,websocket}.ts
```

## API Routes

Backend URL prefix: `/api/v1/`
- Documents app: `/api/v1/documents/{collections,files,chunks}/`
- Chat app: `/api/v1/chat/{sessions,messages,feedback}/`
- Evaluation app: `/api/v1/evaluation/{runs,questions}/`
- WebSocket: `ws://host/ws/chat/<collection_id>/`

## Dev Startup

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Backend
cd backend && source venv/bin/activate && unset GEMINI_API_KEY
daphne -b 0.0.0.0 -p 8000 config.asgi:application

# Terminal 2 — Celery
cd backend && source venv/bin/activate && unset GEMINI_API_KEY
OBJC_DISABLE_INITIALIZE_FORK_SAFETY=YES celery -A config.celery worker -l info --pool=solo

# Terminal 3 — Frontend
cd frontend && npm run dev
```

## Environment Variables (backend/.env)

Required: GEMINI_API_KEY, JINA_API_KEY, DATABASE_URL, SUPABASE_DB_URL, SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_KEY, REDIS_URL
Optional: LANGSMITH_API_KEY, SENTRY_DSN

## Feature Tracking Workflow

When working on a new feature branch:
1. After implementing the feature, UPDATE this file (`.cursor/rules/documind-project.mdc`)
2. Add the feature to the "Implemented Features" list
3. Add any new gotchas to "Critical Implementation Details"
4. Add any new bugs to "Known Issues"
